24/07/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski invited the leaders of the parliamentary opposition parties to join talks on the future constitutional revision and other key political issues, the Macedonian government press office said Friday (22 July). Buckovski sent the invitation to the chairpersons of the three Macedonian formations -- VMRO-DPMNE, VMRO-NP and the Liberal Party, as well as to the ethnic Albanian Party of Democratic Prosperity and Democratic Party of Albanians -- inviting them to the meetings scheduled for next week. The discussions should focus on the draft constitutional amendments related to key judicial reform, the draft law on communications and the current security situation in Macedonia. (Dnevnik, Makfax, A1 TV - 23/07/05)
